  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1771",
  "title": "Is there a way to check if no results exist for multiple index searches?",
  "body": "I have an overall \"All Results\" component that displays search results for multiple categories/index names and we want to display some \"No results\" text if no matching results are found in any category.\r\n\r\nI know you can do that for each individual index, but is there a way to aggregate all of the results together? I'm currently just adding a temporary container that tracks each individual category results and checking if all are have no results but wasn't sure if there's a way to do this already in your plugin.",
